  • RGBAI for Auxiliary & CW+WW for Main: The maximum degree of customization to users that while programming RGB color changing from 16 million colors in the Aulixiary Light, the round Main Light is ONLY tunable 2700k-6500k warm white to cool white for reading or relaxing & 1-100% dimmable brightness. More combinations of lighting effects depend on your ideas
  • Smart App & Voice Control: Manage led can lights for ceiling with Lumary App via Bluetooth & 2.4GHz Wi-Fi. If the light called Kitchen, after synced to Alexa, you will find the Main Light called ''Kitchen'' while the Auxiliary Light called ''Kitchen Colorswitch''. And you can also dim the smart lights individually-Main Light & Auxiliary Light by Alexa, Google Assistant and Siri. The connectivity options of smart home promise more stable and seamless connection and intergrate other smart home devices easily. Note: This model cannot work with Apple Home kit, 5.0 Ghz and dimmer switch
  • Multiple Control Ways: There is more than one way to control Lumary smart wafer lights, including Lumary App (but NOT support Lumary BT Remote), Alexa, Google Assistant, Siri (Not support Homekit, achieve siri control through Lumary App automation function). You can remotely modify your home lighting from anywhere you are, gone are the days when you would patrol around your household to ensure all your lights were off. All Lumary smart lights are NOT suggested to work with any dimmer switch
  • Easy Installation: Just Screw & Push upwards.Equipped new design triangle legs, the installation is like a breeze. Akin to screwing in a regular lightbulb. Push the housing clockwise to finish installation and turn the housing anticlockwise to removal. Besides, plastic body coverd can lights enhancing 50% wi-fi signal stable. Noted, Align the can housing flush with the ceiling. Do not add extra trim for can, Please remove them and finish the easy mounted
  • Spread Joy: Easy sharing without pairing again. Your members can control the recessed lighting together and enjoy the smart fun. With memory, the function will stay at the last setting you choose while turned on again, no need to reset it allows for simultaneous logins on multiple devices
  • Group Control: Control all led can lights for ceiling via the app or smart home easily instead of touching the dimmer switch. You can adjust the lights in separate rooms by making them separate groups. In holiday, you can also turn on/off or dim your lights any time anywhere pretending someone is home. Tips, quickly enter reset mode by physically switching on/off/on

                I installed the Smart 4 Inch LED Recessed Lights in my home about 2 months ago and I couldn't be more satisfied with the performance and versatility they offer.
                The baffle trim design gives a modern look to the lights, making them an excellent addition to any room. Installation was straightforward, and I liked the retrofit capability because it allowed me to easily replace my old can lights without extensive modifications.
                These lights feature a dimmable range of 2700K to 6500K, providing a fantastic spectrum of white light options. Whether I wanted a warm, cozy ambiance or a bright daylight effect, these lights delivered flawlessly. The ability to adjust the brightness is a great feature.
                One of the standout features is the integration with smart home systems. I was able to connect the lights to my Alexa and device. No need to always get up and go to the light switch because I used the voice control which is wonderful convenience.
                There's 66 scene modes offering a wide variety of pre-set options that cater to different occasions like movie nights to dinner parties. It’s fun experimenting with the different scenes.
                As someone who values safety and durability, I appreciate that these lights are soffit damp rated. This feature gives me peace of mind knowing they can withstand moisture, making them suitable for bathrooms too. The lights have exceeded my expectations. With their combination of style, functionality, and smart technology, they are an excellent choice when upgrading your lighting system.

                I really like Lumary lights and have been gradually replacing my old single-color ones with the newer RGBAI models. However, I’ve decided to pause the transition for now. The lights are still high-quality and straightforward to use, but the software doesn’t quite match the hardware’s potential. The Lumary app makes it easy to control the lights, but no one wants to use their phone every time they need to adjust them. The Alexa integration is particularly poor—while the app recognizes each light, Alexa fails to differentiate between the two rings, often resulting in the inside light being controlled unintentionally or the routine doing whatever it feels like.

                They are great lights, they just need some more back end attention.
